<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Spinal processes on body dorsum absent, and marginal processes present or absent on thoracic nota and abdominal tergites I-IV in apterae. Median frontal tubercle protuberant, hemispherical, rectangular, sometimes with a depression at the middle in apterae. Antennae 4- or 5-segmented in apterae. Cauda tongue-shaped with 4 or 5 setae, sometimes with 6 setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The nominate subgenus contains seven species, including three new species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verma" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon harvense" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harvense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon harvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Verma is first recorded in China. This subgenus is mainly distributed in eastern Asia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
